			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>About Interbots</strong><br />
	Interbots is an entertainment robotics startup located in Pittsburgh, PA. Having spent our early years developing innovative control software for high-end animatronics, Interbots is now adapting our technology for the consumer toy market, reinventing robotic play for today&rsquo;s web-savvy generation of kids. We consider technology a tool of the imagination and strive to stimulate children&#39;s creativity and self-expression through customizable robotics, connected applications, and fun content creation tools.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong>About the Position</strong><br />
	As an Interbots&#39; app developer, you are responsible for the implementation of Interbots&#39; software applications, specifically interfacing between mobile devices and robotic hardware.</p>
<p>
	You are a strong, capable programmer with a firm understanding of how implementation decisions affect product flexibility, robustness, and security. You have experience bringing together multiple subsystems into a cohesive working product. You value attention to detail and documentation. You can articulate your ideas clearly in person and thoroughly in writing.</p>
<p>
	You are an enthusiastic and flexible team player. You work closely with the software architect and UI designers to translate gameplay and aesthetic goals into functional realities. You are good at breaking down problems and evaluating potential solutions. You overcome technical blockades through research and creative problem solving.</p>
<p>
	You keep up with latest technologies and trends &ndash; especially in the fields of entertainment technology, mobile devices, toys, robotics, and user interfaces. You like to tinker.</p>
<p>
	You understand that working for a young startup company means tough challenges and strange hours as well as exciting potential rewards and a close-knit team environment.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science or other relevant discipline</li>
	<li>
		3+ years of work experience with references &amp; code samples</li>
	<li>
		Substantial experience developing mobile applications (iOS &amp; Android)</li>
	<li>
		Experience using and/or writing serial/usb port interfaces to hardware</li>
	<li>
		Knowledge of .Net framework (C#) preferred</li>
	<li>
		Ability to take high level goals and break them down into achievable tasks</li>
	<li>
		Ability to work within tight deadlines and deliver requests with a quick turn-around time</li>
	<li>
		Proven success working in collaborative cross‐disciplinary team environments</li>
	<li>
		Located in Pittsburgh or willing to relocate<br />
		&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
